31static const char ALPHABET[] = "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ-. $/+%*";
32
33/**
34* Each character consists of 5 bars and 4 spaces, 3 of which are wide (i.e. 6 are narrow).
35* Each character is followed by a narrow space. The narrow to wide ratio is between 1:2 and 1:3.
36* These represent the encodings of characters, as patterns of wide and narrow bars.
37* The 9 least-significant bits of each int correspond to the pattern of wide and narrow,
38* with 1s representing "wide" and 0s representing "narrow".
39*/
40static const int CHARACTER_ENCODINGS[] = {
41 0x034, 0x121, 0x061, 0x160, 0x031, 0x130, 0x070, 0x025, 0x124, 0x064, // 0-9
42 0x109, 0x049, 0x148, 0x019, 0x118, 0x058, 0x00D, 0x10C, 0x04C, 0x01C, // A-J
43 0x103, 0x043, 0x142, 0x013, 0x112, 0x052, 0x007, 0x106, 0x046, 0x016, // K-T
44 0x181, 0x0C1, 0x1C0, 0x091, 0x190, 0x0D0, 0x085, 0x184, 0x0C4, 0x0A8, // U-$
45 0x0A2, 0x08A, 0x02A, 0x094 // /-% , *
46};
47
48static_assert(Size(ALPHABET) - 1 == Size(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS), "table size mismatch");
49
50static const int ASTERISK_ENCODING = 0x094;
51
52static const char PERCENTAGE_MAPPING[26] = {
53 'A' - 38, 'B' - 38, 'C' - 38, 'D' - 38, 'E' - 38, // %A to %E map to control codes ESC to USep
54 'F' - 11, 'G' - 11, 'H' - 11, 'I' - 11, 'J' - 11, // %F to %J map to ; < = > ?
55 'K' + 16, 'L' + 16, 'M' + 16, 'N' + 16, 'O' + 16, // %K to %O map to [ \ ] ^ _
56 'P' + 43, 'Q' + 43, 'R' + 43, 'S' + 43, 'T' + 43, // %P to %T map to { | } ~ DEL
57 '\0', '@', '`', // %U map to NUL, %V map to @, %W map to `
58 127, 127, 127 // %X to %Z all map to DEL (127)
59};
60
61using CounterContainer = std::array<int, 9>;
62
63// For efficiency, returns -1 on failure. Not throwing here saved as many as 700 exceptions
64// per image when using some of our blackbox images.
65static int
66ToNarrowWidePattern(const CounterContainer& counters)
67{
68 int numCounters = Size(counters);
69 int maxNarrowCounter = 0;
70 int wideCounters;
71 do {
72 int minCounter = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
73 for (int i = 0; i < numCounters; ++i) {
74 if (counters[i] < minCounter && counters[i] > maxNarrowCounter) {
75 minCounter = counters[i];
76 }
77 }
78 maxNarrowCounter = minCounter;
79 wideCounters = 0;
80 int totalWideCountersWidth = 0;
81 int pattern = 0;
82 for (int i = 0; i < numCounters; ++i) {
83 if (counters[i] > maxNarrowCounter) {
84 pattern |= 1 << (numCounters - 1 - i);
85 wideCounters++;
86 totalWideCountersWidth += counters[i];
87 }
88 }
89 if (wideCounters == 3) {
90 // Found 3 wide counters, but are they close enough in width?
91 // We can perform a cheap, conservative check to see if any individual
92 // counter is more than 1.5 times the average:
93 for (int i = 0; i < numCounters && wideCounters > 0; ++i) {
94 if (counters[i] > maxNarrowCounter) {
95 wideCounters--;
96 // totalWideCountersWidth = 3 * average, so this checks if counter >= 3/2 * average
97 if ((counters[i] * 2) >= totalWideCountersWidth) {
98 return -1;
99 }
100 }
101 }
102 return pattern;
103 }
104 } while (wideCounters > 3);
105 return -1;
106}
107
108static BitArray::Range
109FindAsteriskPattern(const BitArray& row)
110{
111 CounterContainer counters;
112
113 return RowReader::FindPattern(
114 row.getNextSet(row.begin()), row.end(), counters,
115 [&row](BitArray::Iterator begin, BitArray::Iterator end, const CounterContainer& counters) {
116 // Look for whitespace before start pattern, >= 50% of width of start pattern
117 return row.hasQuiteZone(begin, static_cast<int>(-(end-begin)/2)) &&
118 ToNarrowWidePattern(counters) == ASTERISK_ENCODING;
119 });
120}
121
122// each character has 5 bars and 4 spaces
123constexpr int CHAR_LEN = 9;
124
125inline bool IsStartOrStopChar(char c)
126{
127 return c == '*';
128}
129
130/** Decode the extended string in place. Return false if FormatError occured.
131 * ctrl is either "$%/+" for code39 or "abcd" for code93. */
132bool
133DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(std::string& encoded, const char ctrl[4])
134{
135 auto out = encoded.begin();
136 for (auto in = encoded.cbegin(); in != encoded.cend(); ++in) {
137 char c = *in;
138 if (Contains(ctrl, c)) {
139 char next = *++in; // if in is one short of cend(), then next == 0
140 if (next < 'A' || next > 'Z')
141 return false;
142 if (c == ctrl[0])
143 c = next - 64; // $A to $Z map to control codes SH to SB
144 else if (c == ctrl[1])
145 c = PERCENTAGE_MAPPING[next - 'A'];
146 else if (c == ctrl[2])
147 c = next - 32; // /A to /O map to ! to , and /Z maps to :
148 else
149 c = next + 32; // +A to +Z map to a to z
150 }
151 *out++ = c;
152 }
153 encoded.erase(out, encoded.end());
154 return true;
155}

157
158Code39Reader::Code39Reader(const DecodeHints& hints) :
159 _extendedMode(hints.tryCode39ExtendedMode()),
160 _usingCheckDigit(hints.assumeCode39CheckDigit())
161{
162}
163
164Result
165Code39Reader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
166{
167 auto range = FindAsteriskPattern(row);
168 if (!range)
169 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
170
171 int xStart = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
172 CounterContainer theCounters = {};
173 std::string result;
174 result.reserve(20);
175
176 do {
177 // Read off white space
178 range = RecordPattern(row.getNextSet(range.end), row.end(), theCounters);
179 if (!range)
180 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
181
182 int pattern = OneD::ToNarrowWidePattern(theCounters);
183 if (pattern < 0)
184 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
185
186 int i = IndexOf(CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, pattern);
187 if (i < 0)
188 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
189
190 result += ALPHABET[i];
191 } while (result.back() != '*');
192
193 result.pop_back(); // remove asterisk
194
195 // Require at least one payload character and a quite zone of half the last pattern size.
196 if (result.size() < (_usingCheckDigit ? 2u : 1u) || !row.hasQuiteZone(range.end, range.size() / 2)) {
197 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
198 }
199
200 if (_usingCheckDigit) {
201 auto checkDigit = result.back();
202 result.pop_back();
203 int checksum = TransformReduce(result, 0, [](char c) { return IndexOf(ALPHABET, c); });
204 if (checkDigit != ALPHABET[checksum % 43]) {
205 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
206 }
207 }
208
209 if (_extendedMode && !DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(result, "$%/+"))
210 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
211
212 int xStop = static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin() - 1);
213 return Result(result, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_39);
214}
215
216// pattern where '1' means 'narrow' and '0' means wide
217constexpr auto START_PATTERN = FixedSparcePattern<CHAR_LEN, 6>{1, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, 1, 1};
218// quite zone is half the width of a character symbol
219constexpr float QUITE_ZONE_SCALE = 0.5f;
220
221Result Code39Reader::decodePattern(int rowNumber, const PatternView& row, std::unique_ptr<RowReader::DecodingState>&) const
222{
223 // minimal number of characters that must be present (including start, stop and checksum characters)
224 int minCharCount = _usingCheckDigit ? 4 : 3;
225 auto isStartOrStopSymbol = [](char c) { return c == '*'; };
226
227 auto next = ZXing::FindPattern(row.subView(0, -minCharCount * CHAR_LEN), START_PATTERN, QUITE_ZONE_SCALE);
228 if (!next.isValid())
229 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
230
231 if (!isStartOrStopSymbol(DecodeNarrowWidePattern(next, CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, ALPHABET))) // read off the start pattern
232 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
233
234 int xStart = next.pixelsInFront();
235 int maxInterCharacterSpace = next.sum() / 2; // spec actually says 1 narrow space, width/2 is about 4
236
237 std::string txt;
238 txt.reserve(20);
239
240 do {
241 // check remaining input width and inter-character space
242 if (!next.skipSymbol() || !next.skipSingle(maxInterCharacterSpace))
243 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
244
245 txt += DecodeNarrowWidePattern(next, CHARACTER_ENCODINGS, ALPHABET);
246 if (txt.back() < 0)
247 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
248 } while (!isStartOrStopSymbol(txt.back()));
249
250 txt.pop_back(); // remove asterisk
251
252 // check txt length and whitespace after the last char. See also FindStartPattern.
253 if (Size(txt) < minCharCount - 2 || !next.hasQuiteZoneAfter(QUITE_ZONE_SCALE))
254 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
255
256 if (_usingCheckDigit) {
257 auto checkDigit = txt.back();
258 txt.pop_back();
259 int checksum = TransformReduce(txt, 0, [](char c) { return IndexOf(ALPHABET, c); });
260 if (checkDigit != ALPHABET[checksum % 43])
261 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
262 }
263
264 if (_extendedMode && !DecodeExtendedCode39AndCode93(txt, "$%/+"))
265 return Result(DecodeStatus::FormatError);
266
267 int xStop = next.pixelsInFront() + next.sum() - 1;
268 return Result(txt, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, BarcodeFormat::CODE_39);
269}
